titleStmt.title: A catalogue of excellent English books in divinity, history, geography, travels, romances poetry, law, physick, mathematicks, &c. Which will be sold by auction at Batson's coffee-house, over-against the Royal Exchange in Corn-Hill, at three of the clock in the afternoon, on Tuesday, June 27. 1693. Catalogues are distributed by Mr. Partridge at Charing-Cross, Mr. Hargrave in Holborn, Mr. Southby in Fleetstreet, Booksellers; and at the place of sale.

notesStmt.note: Reproduction of the original in the British Library.
